#Standard error of the mean
std <- function(x) sd(x)/sqrt(length(x))


scale_this <- function(x){
  (x - mean(x, na.rm=TRUE)) / sd(x, na.rm=TRUE)
}

NOTES from during converstion to a machine readable datafile

McMaster, both departments, provide “more to offset higher tuition” to the international MSc students, but the amount is unspecified.

Summary information

There were 140 programs within the final dataset, from 38 Universities. There are 71 MSc and 69 PhD programs. Of all of these different degree programs, 50.7142857% were classified as closest to Ecology, while 49.2857143% are in Physics.

Mean domestic tuition was 5824.5582857CAD, median 6240.165CAD. Mean international tuition was 1.5408013^{4}CAD, median 1.497777^{4}CAD. Mean domestic fees were 1667.0457576CAD, international mean 2264.8789394CAD. Total tuition and fees domestic mean is 7396.3442857CAD, while international total was 1.7560024^{4}CAD.

Of the 140 programs within the final dataset, 93 programs have a minimum, while 10 had no information provided that we could access and did not respond to our requests. The average domestic minimum stipend provided was 2.3933189^{4}CAD, median 2.415^{4}CAD. When support is different than domestic support, international minimum gross stipend mean is 2.5754566^{4}CAD. Net domestic mean is 1.6674939^{4}CAD while median 1.729052^{4}CAD.

Mean tuition Get score: NA Mean tuition Parse score: NA Mean Stipend Get score: NA Mean Stipend Complete score: NA

Domestic students repay 33.2732171% back to the university in the form of tuition and fees. International students repay 75.9493073% back to the university in the form of tuition and fees.

Mean MBM Shortfall Domestic: -9584.4457851 Mean MBM Shortfall International: -1.6997344^{4}

difference between US and Canada: NA
